59static uint64_t readUint(uint8_t *Buf) {
60 return Config->Is64 ? read64(Buf) : read32(Buf);
61}
62
63static void writeUint(uint8_t *Buf, uint64_t Val) {
64 if (Config->Is64)
65 write64(Buf, Val);
66 else
67 write32(Buf, Val);
68}

70// Returns an LLD version string.
71static ArrayRef<uint8_t> getVersion() {
72 // Check LLD_VERSION first for ease of testing.
73 // You can get consistent output by using the environment variable.
74 // This is only for testing.
75 StringRef S = getenv("LLD_VERSION");
76 if (S.empty())
77 S = Saver.save(Twine("Linker: ") + getLLDVersion());
78
79 // +1 to include the terminating '\0'.
80 return {(const uint8_t *)S.data(), S.size() + 1};
81}

83// Creates a .comment section containing LLD version info.
84// With this feature, you can identify LLD-generated binaries easily
85// by "readelf --string-dump .comment <file>".
86// The returned object is a mergeable string section.
87MergeInputSection *elf::createCommentSection() {
88 return make<MergeInputSection>(SHF_MERGE | SHF_STRINGS, SHT_PROGBITS, 1,
89 getVersion(), ".comment");
90}

92// .MIPS.abiflags section.
93template <class ELFT>
94MipsAbiFlagsSection<ELFT>::MipsAbiFlagsSection(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags Flags)
95 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC, SHT_MIPS_ABIFLAGS, 8, ".MIPS.abiflags"),
96 Flags(Flags) {
97 this->Entsize = sizeof(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags);
98}
99
100template <class ELFT> void MipsAbiFlagsSection<ELFT>::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
101 memcpy(Buf, &Flags, sizeof(Flags));
102}
103
104template <class ELFT>
105MipsAbiFlagsSection<ELFT> *MipsAbiFlagsSection<ELFT>::create() {
106 Elf_Mips_ABIFlags Flags = {};
107 bool Create = false;
108
109 std::string LastFile = "<internal>";
110 for (InputSectionBase *Sec : InputSections) {
111 if (Sec->Type != SHT_MIPS_ABIFLAGS)
112 continue;
113 Sec->markDead();
114 Create = true;
115
116 std::string Filename = toString(Sec->File);
117 const size_t Size = Sec->data().size();
118 // Older version of BFD (such as the default FreeBSD linker) concatenate
119 // .MIPS.abiflags instead of merging. To allow for this case (or potential
120 // zero padding) we ignore everything after the first Elf_Mips_ABIFlags
121 if (Size < sizeof(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags)) {
122 error(Filename + ": invalid size of .MIPS.abiflags section: got " +
123 Twine(Size) + " instead of " + Twine(sizeof(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags)));
124 return nullptr;
125 }
126 auto *S = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Mips_ABIFlags *>(Sec->data().data());
127 if (S->version != 0) {
128 error(Filename + ": unexpected .MIPS.abiflags version " +
129 Twine(S->version));
130 return nullptr;
131 }
132 if (Size > sizeof(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags)) {
133 warn(Filename + ": .MIPS.abiflags section has multiple entries: got " +
134 Twine(Size) + " instead of " + Twine(sizeof(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags)) +
135 " bytes");
136 }
137
138 // LLD checks ISA compatibility in calcMipsEFlags(). Here we just
139 // select the highest number of ISA/Rev/Ext.
140 Flags.isa_level = std::max(Flags.isa_level, S->isa_level);
141 Flags.isa_rev = std::max(Flags.isa_rev, S->isa_rev);
142 Flags.isa_ext =
143 elf::getMipsIsaExt(Flags.isa_ext, LastFile, S->isa_ext, Filename);
144 Flags.gpr_size = std::max(Flags.gpr_size, S->gpr_size);
145 Flags.cpr1_size = std::max(Flags.cpr1_size, S->cpr1_size);
146 Flags.cpr2_size = std::max(Flags.cpr2_size, S->cpr2_size);
147 Flags.ases |= S->ases;
148 Flags.flags1 |= S->flags1;
149 Flags.flags2 |= S->flags2;
150 Flags.fp_abi =
151 elf::getMipsFpAbiFlag(Flags.fp_abi, LastFile, S->fp_abi, Filename);
152 LastFile = std::move(Filename);
153 };
154
155 if (Create)
156 return make<MipsAbiFlagsSection<ELFT>>(Flags);
157 return nullptr;
158}
159
160template <class ELFT>
161Optional<unsigned> MipsAbiFlagsSection<ELFT>::getCheriAbiVariant() const {
162 auto CheriAbiVariant = Flags.isa_ext & Mips::AFL_EXT_CHERI_ABI_MASK;
163 if (!CheriAbiVariant) {
164 warn("Linking old object files without CheriABI variant flag.");
165 return None;
166 }
167 switch (CheriAbiVariant) {
168 case Mips::AFL_EXT_CHERI_ABI_LEGACY:
169 return DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_LEGACY;
170 case Mips::AFL_EXT_CHERI_ABI_PCREL:
171 return DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_PCREL;
172 case Mips::AFL_EXT_CHERI_ABI_PLT:
173 return DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_PLT;
174 case Mips::AFL_EXT_CHERI_ABI_FNDESC:
175 return DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_FNDESC;
176 default:
177 error("Unknown CHERI ABI variant " + Twine(CheriAbiVariant));
178 return None;
179 }
180}

182// .MIPS.options section.
183template <class ELFT>
184MipsOptionsSection<ELFT>::MipsOptionsSection(Elf_Mips_RegInfo Reginfo)
185 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC, SHT_MIPS_OPTIONS, 8, ".MIPS.options"),
186 Reginfo(Reginfo) {
187 this->Entsize = sizeof(Elf_Mips_Options) + sizeof(Elf_Mips_RegInfo);
188}
189
190template <class ELFT> void MipsOptionsSection<ELFT>::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
191 auto *Options = reinterpret_cast<Elf_Mips_Options *>(Buf);
192 Options->kind = ODK_REGINFO;
193 Options->size = getSize();
194
195 if (!Config->Relocatable)
196 Reginfo.ri_gp_value = In.MipsGot->getGp();
197 memcpy(Buf + sizeof(Elf_Mips_Options), &Reginfo, sizeof(Reginfo));
198}
199
200template <class ELFT>
201MipsOptionsSection<ELFT> *MipsOptionsSection<ELFT>::create() {
202 // N64 ABI only.
203 if (!ELFT::Is64Bits)
204 return nullptr;
205
206 std::vector<InputSectionBase *> Sections;
207 for (InputSectionBase *Sec : InputSections)
208 if (Sec->Type == SHT_MIPS_OPTIONS)
209 Sections.push_back(Sec);
210
211 if (Sections.empty())
212 return nullptr;
213
214 Elf_Mips_RegInfo Reginfo = {};
215 for (InputSectionBase *Sec : Sections) {
216 Sec->markDead();
217
218 std::string Filename = toString(Sec->File);
219 ArrayRef<uint8_t> D = Sec->data();
220
221 while (!D.empty()) {
222 if (D.size() < sizeof(Elf_Mips_Options)) {
223 error(Filename + ": invalid size of .MIPS.options section");
224 break;
225 }
226
227 auto *Opt = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Mips_Options *>(D.data());
228 if (Opt->kind == ODK_REGINFO) {
229 Reginfo.ri_gprmask |= Opt->getRegInfo().ri_gprmask;
230 Sec->getFile<ELFT>()->MipsGp0 = Opt->getRegInfo().ri_gp_value;
231 break;
232 }
233
234 if (!Opt->size)
235 fatal(Filename + ": zero option descriptor size");
236 D = D.slice(Opt->size);
237 }
238 };
239
240 return make<MipsOptionsSection<ELFT>>(Reginfo);
241}

244template <class ELFT>
245MipsReginfoSection<ELFT>::MipsReginfoSection(Elf_Mips_RegInfo Reginfo)
246 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC, SHT_MIPS_REGINFO, 4, ".reginfo"),
247 Reginfo(Reginfo) {
248 this->Entsize = sizeof(Elf_Mips_RegInfo);
249}
250
251template <class ELFT> void MipsReginfoSection<ELFT>::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
252 if (!Config->Relocatable)
253 Reginfo.ri_gp_value = In.MipsGot->getGp();
254 memcpy(Buf, &Reginfo, sizeof(Reginfo));
255}
256
257template <class ELFT>
258MipsReginfoSection<ELFT> *MipsReginfoSection<ELFT>::create() {
259 // Section should be alive for O32 and N32 ABIs only.
260 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
261 return nullptr;
262
263 std::vector<InputSectionBase *> Sections;
264 for (InputSectionBase *Sec : InputSections)
265 if (Sec->Type == SHT_MIPS_REGINFO)
266 Sections.push_back(Sec);
267
268 if (Sections.empty())
269 return nullptr;
270
271 Elf_Mips_RegInfo Reginfo = {};
272 for (InputSectionBase *Sec : Sections) {
273 Sec->markDead();
274
275 if (Sec->data().size() != sizeof(Elf_Mips_RegInfo)) {
276 error(toString(Sec->File) + ": invalid size of .reginfo section");
277 return nullptr;
278 }
279
280 auto *R = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Mips_RegInfo *>(Sec->data().data());
281 Reginfo.ri_gprmask |= R->ri_gprmask;
282 Sec->getFile<ELFT>()->MipsGp0 = R->ri_gp_value;
283 };
284
285 return make<MipsReginfoSection<ELFT>>(Reginfo);
286}

288InputSection *elf::createInterpSection() {
289 // StringSaver guarantees that the returned string ends with '\0'.
290 StringRef S = Saver.save(Config->DynamicLinker);
291 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Contents = {(const uint8_t *)S.data(), S.size() + 1};
292
293 auto *Sec = make<InputSection>(nullptr, SHF_ALLOC, SHT_PROGBITS, 1, Contents,
294 ".interp");
295 Sec->markLive();
296 return Sec;
297}

299Defined *elf::addSyntheticLocal(StringRef Name, uint8_t Type, uint64_t Value,
300 uint64_t Size, InputSectionBase &Section) {
301 auto *S = make<Defined>(Section.File, Name, STB_LOCAL, STV_DEFAULT, Type,
302 Value, Size, &Section);
303 if (In.SymTab)
304 In.SymTab->addSymbol(S);
305 return S;
306}

308static size_t getHashSize() {
309 switch (Config->BuildId) {
310 case BuildIdKind::Fast:
311 return 8;
312 case BuildIdKind::Md5:
313 case BuildIdKind::Uuid:
314 return 16;
315 case BuildIdKind::Sha1:
316 return 20;
317 case BuildIdKind::Hexstring:
318 return Config->BuildIdVector.size();
319 default:
320 llvm_unreachable("unknown BuildIdKind");
321 }
322}

324// This class represents a linker-synthesized .note.gnu.property section.
325//
326// In x86 and AArch64, object files may contain feature flags indicating the
327// features that they have used. The flags are stored in a .note.gnu.property
328// section.
329//
330// lld reads the sections from input files and merges them by computing AND of
331// the flags. The result is written as a new .note.gnu.property section.
332//
333// If the flag is zero (which indicates that the intersection of the feature
334// sets is empty, or some input files didn't have .note.gnu.property sections),
335// we don't create this section.
336GnuPropertySection::GnuPropertySection()
337 : SyntheticSection(llvm::ELF::SHF_ALLOC, llvm::ELF::SHT_NOTE, 4,
338 ".note.gnu.property") {}
339
340void GnuPropertySection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
341 uint32_t FeatureAndType = Config->EMachine == EM_AARCH64
342 ? GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_AND
343 : GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_1_AND;
344
345 write32(Buf, 4); // Name size
346 write32(Buf + 4, Config->Is64 ? 16 : 12); // Content size
347 write32(Buf + 8, NT_GNU_PROPERTY_TYPE_0); // Type
348 memcpy(Buf + 12, "GNU", 4); // Name string
349 write32(Buf + 16, FeatureAndType); // Feature type
350 write32(Buf + 20, 4); // Feature size
351 write32(Buf + 24, Config->AndFeatures); // Feature flags
352 if (Config->Is64)
353 write32(Buf + 28, 0); // Padding
354}
355
356size_t GnuPropertySection::getSize() const { return Config->Is64 ? 32 : 28; }
357
358BuildIdSection::BuildIdSection()
359 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC, SHT_NOTE, 4, ".note.gnu.build-id"),
360 HashSize(getHashSize()) {}
361
362void BuildIdSection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
363 write32(Buf, 4); // Name size
364 write32(Buf + 4, HashSize); // Content size
365 write32(Buf + 8, NT_GNU_BUILD_ID); // Type
366 memcpy(Buf + 12, "GNU", 4); // Name string
367 HashBuf = Buf + 16;
368}
369
370void BuildIdSection::writeBuildId(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Buf) {
371 assert(Buf.size() == HashSize);
372 memcpy(HashBuf, Buf.data(), HashSize);
373}

384// Search for an existing CIE record or create a new one.
385// CIE records from input object files are uniquified by their contents
386// and where their relocations point to.
387template <class ELFT, class RelTy>
388CieRecord *EhFrameSection::addCie(EhSectionPiece &Cie, ArrayRef<RelTy> Rels) {
389 Symbol *Personality = nullptr;
390 unsigned FirstRelI = Cie.FirstRelocation;
391 if (FirstRelI != (unsigned)-1)
392 Personality =
393 &Cie.Sec->template getFile<ELFT>()->getRelocTargetSym(Rels[FirstRelI]);
394
395 // Search for an existing CIE by CIE contents/relocation target pair.
396 CieRecord *&Rec = CieMap[{Cie.data(), Personality}];
397
398 // If not found, create a new one.
399 if (!Rec) {
400 Rec = make<CieRecord>();
401 Rec->Cie = &Cie;
402 CieRecords.push_back(Rec);
403 }
404 return Rec;
405}

407// There is one FDE per function. Returns true if a given FDE
408// points to a live function.
409template <class ELFT, class RelTy>
410bool EhFrameSection::isFdeLive(EhSectionPiece &Fde, ArrayRef<RelTy> Rels) {
411 auto *Sec = cast<EhInputSection>(Fde.Sec);
412 unsigned FirstRelI = Fde.FirstRelocation;
413
414 // An FDE should point to some function because FDEs are to describe
415 // functions. That's however not always the case due to an issue of
416 // ld.gold with -r. ld.gold may discard only functions and leave their
417 // corresponding FDEs, which results in creating bad .eh_frame sections.
418 // To deal with that, we ignore such FDEs.
419 if (FirstRelI == (unsigned)-1)
420 return false;
421
422 const RelTy &Rel = Rels[FirstRelI];
423 Symbol &B = Sec->template getFile<ELFT>()->getRelocTargetSym(Rel);
424
425 // FDEs for garbage-collected or merged-by-ICF sections, or sections in
426 // another partition, are dead.
427 if (auto *D = dyn_cast<Defined>(&B))
428 if (SectionBase *Sec = D->Section)
429 return Sec->Partition == Partition;
430 return false;
431}
432
433// .eh_frame is a sequence of CIE or FDE records. In general, there
434// is one CIE record per input object file which is followed by
435// a list of FDEs. This function searches an existing CIE or create a new
436// one and associates FDEs to the CIE.
437template <class ELFT, class RelTy>
438void EhFrameSection::addSectionAux(EhInputSection *Sec, ArrayRef<RelTy> Rels) {
439 OffsetToCie.clear();
440 for (EhSectionPiece &Piece : Sec->Pieces) {
441 // The empty record is the end marker.
442 if (Piece.Size == 4)
443 return;
444
445 size_t Offset = Piece.InputOff;
446 uint32_t ID = read32(Piece.data().data() + 4);
447 if (ID == 0) {
448 OffsetToCie[Offset] = addCie<ELFT>(Piece, Rels);
449 continue;
450 }
451
452 uint32_t CieOffset = Offset + 4 - ID;
453 CieRecord *Rec = OffsetToCie[CieOffset];
454 if (!Rec)
455 fatal(toString(Sec) + ": invalid CIE reference");
456
457 if (!isFdeLive<ELFT>(Piece, Rels))
458 continue;
459 Rec->Fdes.push_back(&Piece);
460 NumFdes++;
461 }
462}
463
464template <class ELFT> void EhFrameSection::addSection(InputSectionBase *C) {
465 auto *Sec = cast<EhInputSection>(C);
466 Sec->Parent = this;
467
468 Alignment = std::max(Alignment, Sec->Alignment);
469 // TODO: ideally we should only make .eh_frame writable if we have any dynamic
470 // relocations against it.
471 if (Sec->Flags & SHF_WRITE)
472 Flags |= SHF_WRITE; // TODO: Or should we just do Flags |= Sec->Flags?
473 Sections.push_back(Sec);
474
475 for (auto *DS : Sec->DependentSections)
476 DependentSections.push_back(DS);
477
478 if (Sec->Pieces.empty())
479 return;
480
481 if (Sec->AreRelocsRela)
482 addSectionAux<ELFT>(Sec, Sec->template relas<ELFT>());
483 else
484 addSectionAux<ELFT>(Sec, Sec->template rels<ELFT>());
485}
486
487static void writeCieFde(uint8_t *Buf, ArrayRef<uint8_t> D) {
488 memcpy(Buf, D.data(), D.size());
489
490 size_t Aligned = alignTo(D.size(), Config->Wordsize);
491
492 // Zero-clear trailing padding if it exists.
493 memset(Buf + D.size(), 0, Aligned - D.size());
494
495 // Fix the size field. -4 since size does not include the size field itself.
496 write32(Buf, Aligned - 4);
497}
498
499void EhFrameSection::finalizeContents() {
500 assert(!this->Size); // Not finalized.
501 size_t Off = 0;
502 for (CieRecord *Rec : CieRecords) {
503 Rec->Cie->OutputOff = Off;
504 Off += alignTo(Rec->Cie->Size, Config->Wordsize);
505
506 for (EhSectionPiece *Fde : Rec->Fdes) {
507 Fde->OutputOff = Off;
508 Off += alignTo(Fde->Size, Config->Wordsize);
509 }
510 }
511
512 // The LSB standard does not allow a .eh_frame section with zero
513 // Call Frame Information records. glibc unwind-dw2-fde.c
514 // classify_object_over_fdes expects there is a CIE record length 0 as a
515 // terminator. Thus we add one unconditionally.
516 Off += 4;
517
518 this->Size = Off;
519}
520
521// Returns data for .eh_frame_hdr. .eh_frame_hdr is a binary search table
522// to get an FDE from an address to which FDE is applied. This function
523// returns a list of such pairs.
524std::vector<EhFrameSection::FdeData> EhFrameSection::getFdeData() const {
525 uint8_t *Buf = Out::BufferStart + getParent()->Offset + OutSecOff;
526 std::vector<FdeData> Ret;
527
528 uint64_t VA = getPartition().EhFrameHdr->getVA();
529 for (CieRecord *Rec : CieRecords) {
530 uint8_t Enc = getFdeEncoding(Rec->Cie);
531 for (EhSectionPiece *Fde : Rec->Fdes) {
532 uint64_t Pc = getFdePc(Buf, Fde->OutputOff, Enc);
533 uint64_t FdeVA = getParent()->Addr + Fde->OutputOff;
534 if (!isInt<32>(Pc - VA))
535 fatal(toString(Fde->Sec) + ": PC offset is too large: 0x" +
536 Twine::utohexstr(Pc - VA));
537 Ret.push_back({uint32_t(Pc - VA), uint32_t(FdeVA - VA)});
538 }
539 }
540
541 // Sort the FDE list by their PC and uniqueify. Usually there is only
542 // one FDE for a PC (i.e. function), but if ICF merges two functions
543 // into one, there can be more than one FDEs pointing to the address.
544 auto Less = [](const FdeData &A, const FdeData &B) {
545 return A.PcRel < B.PcRel;
546 };
547 llvm::stable_sort(Ret, Less);
548 auto Eq = [](const FdeData &A, const FdeData &B) {
549 return A.PcRel == B.PcRel;
550 };
551 Ret.erase(std::unique(Ret.begin(), Ret.end(), Eq), Ret.end());
552
553 return Ret;
554}
555
556static uint64_t readFdeAddr(uint8_t *Buf, int Size) {
557 switch (Size) {
558 case DW_EH_PE_udata2:
559 return read16(Buf);
560 case DW_EH_PE_sdata2:
561 return (int16_t)read16(Buf);
562 case DW_EH_PE_udata4:
563 return read32(Buf);
564 case DW_EH_PE_sdata4:
565 return (int32_t)read32(Buf);
566 case DW_EH_PE_udata8:
567 case DW_EH_PE_sdata8:
568 return read64(Buf);
569 case DW_EH_PE_absptr:
570 return readUint(Buf);
571 }
572 fatal("unknown FDE size encoding");
573}
574
575// Returns the VA to which a given FDE (on a mmap'ed buffer) is applied to.
576// We need it to create .eh_frame_hdr section.
577uint64_t EhFrameSection::getFdePc(uint8_t *Buf, size_t FdeOff,
578 uint8_t Enc) const {
579 // The starting address to which this FDE applies is
580 // stored at FDE + 8 byte.
581 size_t Off = FdeOff + 8;
582 uint64_t Addr = readFdeAddr(Buf + Off, Enc & 0xf);
583 if ((Enc & 0x70) == DW_EH_PE_absptr)
584 return Addr;
585 if ((Enc & 0x70) == DW_EH_PE_pcrel)
586 return Addr + getParent()->Addr + Off;
587 fatal("unknown FDE size relative encoding");
588}
589
590void EhFrameSection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
591 // Write CIE and FDE records.
592 for (CieRecord *Rec : CieRecords) {
593 size_t CieOffset = Rec->Cie->OutputOff;
594 writeCieFde(Buf + CieOffset, Rec->Cie->data());
595
596 for (EhSectionPiece *Fde : Rec->Fdes) {
597 size_t Off = Fde->OutputOff;
598 writeCieFde(Buf + Off, Fde->data());
599
600 // FDE's second word should have the offset to an associated CIE.
601 // Write it.
602 write32(Buf + Off + 4, Off + 4 - CieOffset);
603 }
604 }
605
606 // Apply relocations. .eh_frame section contents are not contiguous
607 // in the output buffer, but relocateAlloc() still works because
608 // getOffset() takes care of discontiguous section pieces.
609 for (EhInputSection *S : Sections)
610 S->relocateAlloc(Buf, nullptr);
611
612 if (getPartition().EhFrameHdr && getPartition().EhFrameHdr->getParent())
613 getPartition().EhFrameHdr->write();
614}

616GotSection::GotSection()
617 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC | SHF_WRITE, SHT_PROGBITS, Config->Wordsize,
618 ".got") {
619 // PPC64 saves the ElfSym::GlobalOffsetTable .TOC. as the first entry in the
620 // .got. If there are no references to .TOC. in the symbol table,
621 // ElfSym::GlobalOffsetTable will not be defined and we won't need to save
622 // .TOC. in the .got. When it is defined, we increase NumEntries by the number
623 // of entries used to emit ElfSym::GlobalOffsetTable.
624 if (ElfSym::GlobalOffsetTable && !Target->GotBaseSymInGotPlt)
625 NumEntries += Target->GotHeaderEntriesNum;
626}
627
628void GotSection::addEntry(Symbol &Sym) {
629 Sym.GotIndex = NumEntries;
630 ++NumEntries;
631}
632
633bool GotSection::addDynTlsEntry(Symbol &Sym) {
634 if (Sym.GlobalDynIndex != -1U)
635 return false;
636 Sym.GlobalDynIndex = NumEntries;
637 // Global Dynamic TLS entries take two GOT slots.
638 NumEntries += 2;
639 return true;
640}
641
642// Reserves TLS entries for a TLS module ID and a TLS block offset.
643// In total it takes two GOT slots.
644bool GotSection::addTlsIndex() {
645 if (TlsIndexOff != uint32_t(-1))
646 return false;
647 TlsIndexOff = NumEntries * Config->Wordsize;
648 NumEntries += 2;
649 return true;
650}
651
652uint64_t GotSection::getGlobalDynAddr(const Symbol &B) const {
653 return this->getVA() + B.GlobalDynIndex * Config->Wordsize;
654}
655
656uint64_t GotSection::getGlobalDynOffset(const Symbol &B) const {
657 return B.GlobalDynIndex * Config->Wordsize;
658}
659
660void GotSection::finalizeContents() {
661 Size = NumEntries * Config->Wordsize;
662}
663
664bool GotSection::isNeeded() const {
665 // We need to emit a GOT even if it's empty if there's a relocation that is
666 // relative to GOT(such as GOTOFFREL).
667 return NumEntries || HasGotOffRel;
668}
669
670void GotSection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
671 // Buf points to the start of this section's buffer,
672 // whereas InputSectionBase::relocateAlloc() expects its argument
673 // to point to the start of the output section.
674 Target->writeGotHeader(Buf);
675 relocateAlloc(Buf - OutSecOff, Buf - OutSecOff + Size);
676}
677
678static uint64_t getMipsPageAddr(uint64_t Addr) {
679 return (Addr + 0x8000) & ~0xffff;
680}
681
682static uint64_t getMipsPageCount(uint64_t Size) {
683 return (Size + 0xfffe) / 0xffff + 1;
684}
685
686MipsGotSection::MipsGotSection()
687 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC | SHF_WRITE | SHF_MIPS_GPREL, SHT_PROGBITS, 16,
688 ".got") {}
689
690void MipsGotSection::addEntry(InputFile &File, Symbol &Sym, int64_t Addend,
691 RelExpr Expr) {
692 FileGot &G = getGot(File);
693 if (Expr == R_MIPS_GOT_LOCAL_PAGE) {
694 if (const OutputSection *OS = Sym.getOutputSection())
695 G.PagesMap.insert({OS, {}});
696 else
697 G.Local16.insert({{nullptr, getMipsPageAddr(Sym.getVA(Addend))}, 0});
698 } else if (Sym.isTls())
699 G.Tls.insert({&Sym, 0});
700 else if (Sym.IsPreemptible && Expr == R_ABS)
701 G.Relocs.insert({&Sym, 0});
702 else if (Sym.IsPreemptible)
703 G.Global.insert({&Sym, 0});
704 else if (Expr == R_MIPS_GOT_OFF32)
705 G.Local32.insert({{&Sym, Addend}, 0});
706 else
707 G.Local16.insert({{&Sym, Addend}, 0});
708}
709
710void MipsGotSection::addDynTlsEntry(InputFile &File, Symbol &Sym) {
711 getGot(File).DynTlsSymbols.insert({&Sym, 0});
712}
713
714void MipsGotSection::addTlsIndex(InputFile &File) {
715 getGot(File).DynTlsSymbols.insert({nullptr, 0});
716}
717
718size_t MipsGotSection::FileGot::getEntriesNum() const {
719 return getPageEntriesNum() + Local16.size() + Global.size() + Relocs.size() +
720 Tls.size() + DynTlsSymbols.size() * 2;
721}
722
723size_t MipsGotSection::FileGot::getPageEntriesNum() const {
724 size_t Num = 0;
725 for (const std::pair<const OutputSection *, FileGot::PageBlock> &P : PagesMap)
726 Num += P.second.Count;
727 return Num;
728}
729
730size_t MipsGotSection::FileGot::getIndexedEntriesNum() const {
731 size_t Count = getPageEntriesNum() + Local16.size() + Global.size();
732 // If there are relocation-only entries in the GOT, TLS entries
733 // are allocated after them. TLS entries should be addressable
734 // by 16-bit index so count both reloc-only and TLS entries.
735 if (!Tls.empty() || !DynTlsSymbols.empty())
736 Count += Relocs.size() + Tls.size() + DynTlsSymbols.size() * 2;
737 return Count;
738}
739
740MipsGotSection::FileGot &MipsGotSection::getGot(InputFile &F) {
741 if (!F.MipsGotIndex.hasValue()) {
742 Gots.emplace_back();
743 Gots.back().File = &F;
744 F.MipsGotIndex = Gots.size() - 1;
745 }
746 return Gots[*F.MipsGotIndex];
747}
748
749uint64_t MipsGotSection::getPageEntryOffset(const InputFile *F,
750 const Symbol &Sym,
751 int64_t Addend) const {
752 const FileGot &G = Gots[*F->MipsGotIndex];
753 uint64_t Index = 0;
754 if (const OutputSection *OutSec = Sym.getOutputSection()) {
755 uint64_t SecAddr = getMipsPageAddr(OutSec->Addr);
756 uint64_t SymAddr = getMipsPageAddr(Sym.getVA(Addend));
757 Index = G.PagesMap.lookup(OutSec).FirstIndex + (SymAddr - SecAddr) / 0xffff;
758 } else {
759 Index = G.Local16.lookup({nullptr, getMipsPageAddr(Sym.getVA(Addend))});
760 }
761 return Index * Config->Wordsize;
762}
763
764uint64_t MipsGotSection::getSymEntryOffset(const InputFile *F, const Symbol &S,
765 int64_t Addend) const {
766 const FileGot &G = Gots[*F->MipsGotIndex];
767 Symbol *Sym = const_cast<Symbol *>(&S);
768 if (Sym->isTls())
769 return G.Tls.lookup(Sym) * Config->Wordsize;
770 if (Sym->IsPreemptible)
771 return G.Global.lookup(Sym) * Config->Wordsize;
772 return G.Local16.lookup({Sym, Addend}) * Config->Wordsize;
773}
774
775uint64_t MipsGotSection::getTlsIndexOffset(const InputFile *F) const {
776 const FileGot &G = Gots[*F->MipsGotIndex];
777 return G.DynTlsSymbols.lookup(nullptr) * Config->Wordsize;
778}
779
780uint64_t MipsGotSection::getGlobalDynOffset(const InputFile *F,
781 const Symbol &S) const {
782 const FileGot &G = Gots[*F->MipsGotIndex];
783 Symbol *Sym = const_cast<Symbol *>(&S);
784 return G.DynTlsSymbols.lookup(Sym) * Config->Wordsize;
785}
786
787const Symbol *MipsGotSection::getFirstGlobalEntry() const {
788 if (Gots.empty())
789 return nullptr;
790 const FileGot &PrimGot = Gots.front();
791 if (!PrimGot.Global.empty())
792 return PrimGot.Global.front().first;
793 if (!PrimGot.Relocs.empty())
794 return PrimGot.Relocs.front().first;
795 return nullptr;
796}
797
798unsigned MipsGotSection::getLocalEntriesNum() const {
799 if (Gots.empty())
800 return HeaderEntriesNum;
801 return HeaderEntriesNum + Gots.front().getPageEntriesNum() +
802 Gots.front().Local16.size();
803}
804
805bool MipsGotSection::tryMergeGots(FileGot &Dst, FileGot &Src, bool IsPrimary) {
806 FileGot Tmp = Dst;
807 set_union(Tmp.PagesMap, Src.PagesMap);
808 set_union(Tmp.Local16, Src.Local16);
809 set_union(Tmp.Global, Src.Global);
810 set_union(Tmp.Relocs, Src.Relocs);
811 set_union(Tmp.Tls, Src.Tls);
812 set_union(Tmp.DynTlsSymbols, Src.DynTlsSymbols);
813
814 size_t Count = IsPrimary ? HeaderEntriesNum : 0;
815 Count += Tmp.getIndexedEntriesNum();
816
817 if (Count * Config->Wordsize > Config->MipsGotSize)
818 return false;
819
820 std::swap(Tmp, Dst);
821 return true;
822}
823
824void MipsGotSection::finalizeContents() { updateAllocSize(); }
825
826bool MipsGotSection::updateAllocSize() {
827 Size = HeaderEntriesNum * Config->Wordsize;
828 for (const FileGot &G : Gots)
829 Size += G.getEntriesNum() * Config->Wordsize;
830 return false;
831}
832
833void MipsGotSection::build() {
834 if (Gots.empty())
835 return;
836
837 std::vector<FileGot> MergedGots(1);
838
839 // For each GOT move non-preemptible symbols from the `Global`
840 // to `Local16` list. Preemptible symbol might become non-preemptible
841 // one if, for example, it gets a related copy relocation.
842 for (FileGot &Got : Gots) {
843 for (auto &P: Got.Global)
844 if (!P.first->IsPreemptible)
845 Got.Local16.insert({{P.first, 0}, 0});
846 Got.Global.remove_if([&](const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P) {
847 return !P.first->IsPreemptible;
848 });
849 }
850
851 // For each GOT remove "reloc-only" entry if there is "global"
852 // entry for the same symbol. And add local entries which indexed
853 // using 32-bit value at the end of 16-bit entries.
854 for (FileGot &Got : Gots) {
855 Got.Relocs.remove_if([&](const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P) {
856 return Got.Global.count(P.first);
857 });
858 set_union(Got.Local16, Got.Local32);
859 Got.Local32.clear();
860 }
861
862 // Evaluate number of "reloc-only" entries in the resulting GOT.
863 // To do that put all unique "reloc-only" and "global" entries
864 // from all GOTs to the future primary GOT.
865 FileGot *PrimGot = &MergedGots.front();
866 for (FileGot &Got : Gots) {
867 set_union(PrimGot->Relocs, Got.Global);
868 set_union(PrimGot->Relocs, Got.Relocs);
869 Got.Relocs.clear();
870 }
871
872 // Evaluate number of "page" entries in each GOT.
873 for (FileGot &Got : Gots) {
874 for (std::pair<const OutputSection *, FileGot::PageBlock> &P :
875 Got.PagesMap) {
876 const OutputSection *OS = P.first;
877 uint64_t SecSize = 0;
878 for (BaseCommand *Cmd : OS->SectionCommands) {
879 if (auto *ISD = dyn_cast<InputSectionDescription>(Cmd))
880 for (InputSection *IS : ISD->Sections) {
881 uint64_t Off = alignTo(SecSize, IS->Alignment);
882 SecSize = Off + IS->getSize();
883 }
884 }
885 P.second.Count = getMipsPageCount(SecSize);
886 }
887 }
888
889 // Merge GOTs. Try to join as much as possible GOTs but do not exceed
890 // maximum GOT size. At first, try to fill the primary GOT because
891 // the primary GOT can be accessed in the most effective way. If it
892 // is not possible, try to fill the last GOT in the list, and finally
893 // create a new GOT if both attempts failed.
894 for (FileGot &SrcGot : Gots) {
895 InputFile *File = SrcGot.File;
896 if (tryMergeGots(MergedGots.front(), SrcGot, true)) {
897 File->MipsGotIndex = 0;
898 } else {
899 // If this is the first time we failed to merge with the primary GOT,
900 // MergedGots.back() will also be the primary GOT. We must make sure not
901 // to try to merge again with IsPrimary=false, as otherwise, if the
902 // inputs are just right, we could allow the primary GOT to become 1 or 2
903 // words too big due to ignoring the header size.
904 if (MergedGots.size() == 1 ||
905 !tryMergeGots(MergedGots.back(), SrcGot, false)) {
906 MergedGots.emplace_back();
907 std::swap(MergedGots.back(), SrcGot);
908 }
909 File->MipsGotIndex = MergedGots.size() - 1;
910 }
911 }
912 std::swap(Gots, MergedGots);
913
914 // Reduce number of "reloc-only" entries in the primary GOT
915 // by substracting "global" entries exist in the primary GOT.
916 PrimGot = &Gots.front();
917 PrimGot->Relocs.remove_if([&](const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P) {
918 return PrimGot->Global.count(P.first);
919 });
920
921 // Calculate indexes for each GOT entry.
922 size_t Index = HeaderEntriesNum;
923 for (FileGot &Got : Gots) {
924 Got.StartIndex = &Got == PrimGot ? 0 : Index;
925 for (std::pair<const OutputSection *, FileGot::PageBlock> &P :
926 Got.PagesMap) {
927 // For each output section referenced by GOT page relocations calculate
928 // and save into PagesMap an upper bound of MIPS GOT entries required
929 // to store page addresses of local symbols. We assume the worst case -
930 // each 64kb page of the output section has at least one GOT relocation
931 // against it. And take in account the case when the section intersects
932 // page boundaries.
933 P.second.FirstIndex = Index;
934 Index += P.second.Count;
935 }
936 for (auto &P: Got.Local16)
937 P.second = Index++;
938 for (auto &P: Got.Global)
939 P.second = Index++;
940 for (auto &P: Got.Relocs)
941 P.second = Index++;
942 for (auto &P: Got.Tls)
943 P.second = Index++;
944 for (auto &P: Got.DynTlsSymbols) {
945 P.second = Index;
946 Index += 2;
947 }
948 }
949
950 // Update Symbol::GotIndex field to use this
951 // value later in the `sortMipsSymbols` function.
952 for (auto &P : PrimGot->Global)
953 P.first->GotIndex = P.second;
954 for (auto &P : PrimGot->Relocs)
955 P.first->GotIndex = P.second;
956
957 // Create dynamic relocations.
958 for (FileGot &Got : Gots) {
959 // Create dynamic relocations for TLS entries.
960 for (std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P : Got.Tls) {
961 Symbol *S = P.first;
962 uint64_t Offset = P.second * Config->Wordsize;
963 if (S->IsPreemptible)
964 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc(Target->TlsGotRel, this, Offset, S);
965 }
966 for (std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P : Got.DynTlsSymbols) {
967 Symbol *S = P.first;
968 uint64_t Offset = P.second * Config->Wordsize;
969 if (S == nullptr) {
970 if (!Config->Pic)
971 continue;
972 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc(Target->TlsModuleIndexRel, this, Offset, S);
973 } else {
974 // When building a shared library we still need a dynamic relocation
975 // for the module index. Therefore only checking for
976 // S->IsPreemptible is not sufficient (this happens e.g. for
977 // thread-locals that have been marked as local through a linker script)
978 if (!S->IsPreemptible && !Config->Pic)
979 continue;
980 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc(Target->TlsModuleIndexRel, this, Offset, S);
981 // However, we can skip writing the TLS offset reloc for non-preemptible
982 // symbols since it is known even in shared libraries
983 if (!S->IsPreemptible)
984 continue;
985 Offset += Config->Wordsize;
986 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc(Target->TlsOffsetRel, this, Offset, S);
987 }
988 }
989
990 // Do not create dynamic relocations for non-TLS
991 // entries in the primary GOT.
992 if (&Got == PrimGot)
993 continue;
994
995 // Dynamic relocations for "global" entries.
996 for (const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P : Got.Global) {
997 uint64_t Offset = P.second * Config->Wordsize;
998 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc(Target->RelativeRel, this, Offset, P.first);
999 }
1000 if (!Config->Pic)
1001 continue;
1002 // Dynamic relocations for "local" entries in case of PIC.
1003 for (const std::pair<const OutputSection *, FileGot::PageBlock> &L :
1004 Got.PagesMap) {
1005 size_t PageCount = L.second.Count;
1006 for (size_t PI = 0; PI < PageCount; ++PI) {
1007 uint64_t Offset = (L.second.FirstIndex + PI) * Config->Wordsize;
1008 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc({Target->RelativeRel, this, Offset, L.first,
1009 int64_t(PI * 0x10000)});
1010 }
1011 }
1012 for (const std::pair<GotEntry, size_t> &P : Got.Local16) {
1013 uint64_t Offset = P.second * Config->Wordsize;
1014 Main->RelaDyn->addReloc({Target->RelativeRel, this, Offset, true,
1015 P.first.first, P.first.second});
1016 }
1017 }
1018}

1020bool MipsGotSection::isNeeded() const {
1021 // We add the .got section to the result for dynamic MIPS target because
1022 // its address and properties are mentioned in the .dynamic section.
1023 return !Config->Relocatable;
1024}

1026uint64_t MipsGotSection::getGp(const InputFile *F) const {
1027 // For files without related GOT or files refer a primary GOT
1028 // returns "common" _gp value. For secondary GOTs calculate
1029 // individual _gp values.
1030 if (!F || !F->MipsGotIndex.hasValue() || *F->MipsGotIndex == 0)
1031 return ElfSym::MipsGp->getVA(0);
1032 return getVA() + Gots[*F->MipsGotIndex].StartIndex * Config->Wordsize +
1033 0x7ff0;
1034}
1035
1036void MipsGotSection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
1037 // Set the MSB of the second GOT slot. This is not required by any
1038 // MIPS ABI documentation, though.
1039 //
1040 // There is a comment in glibc saying that "The MSB of got[1] of a
1041 // gnu object is set to identify gnu objects," and in GNU gold it
1042 // says "the second entry will be used by some runtime loaders".
1043 // But how this field is being used is unclear.
1044 //
1045 // We are not really willing to mimic other linkers behaviors
1046 // without understanding why they do that, but because all files
1047 // generated by GNU tools have this special GOT value, and because
1048 // we've been doing this for years, it is probably a safe bet to
1049 // keep doing this for now. We really need to revisit this to see
1050 // if we had to do this.
1051 writeUint(Buf + Config->Wordsize, (uint64_t)1 << (Config->Wordsize * 8 - 1));
1052 for (const FileGot &G : Gots) {
1053 auto Write = [&](size_t I, const Symbol *S, int64_t A) {
1054 uint64_t VA = A;
1055 if (S)
1056 VA = S->getVA(A);
1057 writeUint(Buf + I * Config->Wordsize, VA);
1058 };
1059 // Write 'page address' entries to the local part of the GOT.
1060 for (const std::pair<const OutputSection *, FileGot::PageBlock> &L :
1061 G.PagesMap) {
1062 size_t PageCount = L.second.Count;
1063 uint64_t FirstPageAddr = getMipsPageAddr(L.first->Addr);
1064 for (size_t PI = 0; PI < PageCount; ++PI)
1065 Write(L.second.FirstIndex + PI, nullptr, FirstPageAddr + PI * 0x10000);
1066 }
1067 // Local, global, TLS, reloc-only entries.
1068 // If TLS entry has a corresponding dynamic relocations, leave it
1069 // initialized by zero. Write down adjusted TLS symbol's values otherwise.
1070 // To calculate the adjustments use offsets for thread-local storage.
1071 // https://www.linux-mips.org/wiki/NPTL
1072 for (const std::pair<GotEntry, size_t> &P : G.Local16)
1073 Write(P.second, P.first.first, P.first.second);
1074 // Write VA to the primary GOT only. For secondary GOTs that
1075 // will be done by REL32 dynamic relocations.
1076 if (&G == &Gots.front())
1077 for (const std::pair<const Symbol *, size_t> &P : G.Global)
1078 Write(P.second, P.first, 0);
1079 for (const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P : G.Relocs)
1080 Write(P.second, P.first, 0);
1081 // In the legacy CHERI ABI we still use the GOT for TLS so we need
1082 // to write offset 0 instead of -0x7000 to match the captable.
1083 for (const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P : G.Tls)
1084 Write(P.second, P.first,
1085 (P.first->IsPreemptible || Config->isCheriABI()) ? 0 : -0x7000);
1086 for (const std::pair<Symbol *, size_t> &P : G.DynTlsSymbols) {
1087 if (P.first == nullptr && !Config->Pic)
1088 Write(P.second, nullptr, 1);
1089 else if (P.first && !P.first->IsPreemptible) {
1090 // If we are emitting PIC code with relocations we mustn't write
1091 // anything to the GOT here. When using Elf_Rel relocations the value
1092 // one will be treated as an addend and will cause crashes at runtime
1093 if (!Config->Pic)
1094 Write(P.second, nullptr, 1);
1095 // In the legacy CHERI ABI we still use the GOT for TLS so we need
1096 // to write offset 0 instead of -0x8000 to match the captable.
1097 Write(P.second + 1, P.first, Config->isCheriABI() ? 0 : -0x8000);
1098 }
1099 }
1100 }
1101}

1103// On PowerPC the .plt section is used to hold the table of function addresses
1104// instead of the .got.plt, and the type is SHT_NOBITS similar to a .bss

1106// consitent across both 64-bit PowerPC ABIs as well as the 32-bit PowerPC ABI.

1114 Name = ".plt";

1178StringTableSection::StringTableSection(StringRef Name, bool Dynamic)
1179 : SyntheticSection(Dynamic ? (uint64_t)SHF_ALLOC : 0, SHT_STRTAB, 1, Name),
1180 Dynamic(Dynamic) {
1181 // ELF string tables start with a NUL byte.
1182 addString("");
1183}
1184
1185// Adds a string to the string table. If HashIt is true we hash and check for
1186// duplicates. It is optional because the name of global symbols are already
1187// uniqued and hashing them again has a big cost for a small value: uniquing
1188// them with some other string that happens to be the same.
1189unsigned StringTableSection::addString(StringRef S, bool HashIt) {
1190 if (HashIt) {
1191 auto R = StringMap.insert(std::make_pair(S, this->Size));
1192 if (!R.second)
1193 return R.first->second;
1194 }
1195 unsigned Ret = this->Size;
1196 this->Size = this->Size + S.size() + 1;
1197 Strings.push_back(S);
1198 return Ret;
1199}
1200
1201void StringTableSection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
1202 for (StringRef S : Strings) {
1203 memcpy(Buf, S.data(), S.size());
1204 Buf[S.size()] = '\0';
1205 Buf += S.size() + 1;
1206 }
1207}

1209// Returns the number of version definition entries. Because the first entry
1210// is for the version definition itself, it is the number of versioned symbols
1211// plus one. Note that we don't support multiple versions yet.
1212static unsigned getVerDefNum() { return Config->VersionDefinitions.size() + 1; }

1214template <class ELFT>
1215DynamicSection<ELFT>::DynamicSection()
1216 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC | SHF_WRITE, SHT_DYNAMIC, Config->Wordsize,
1217 ".dynamic") {
1218 this->Entsize = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 16 : 8;
1219
1220 // .dynamic section is not writable on MIPS and on Fuchsia OS
1221 // which passes -z rodynamic.
1222 // See "Special Section" in Chapter 4 in the following document:
1223 // ftp://www.linux-mips.org/pub/linux/mips/doc/ABI/mipsabi.pdf
1224 if (Config->EMachine == EM_MIPS || Config->ZRodynamic)
1225 this->Flags = SHF_ALLOC;
1226}

1228template <class ELFT>
1229void DynamicSection<ELFT>::add(int32_t Tag, std::function<uint64_t()> Fn) {
1230 Entries.push_back({Tag, Fn});
1231}

1233template <class ELFT>
1234void DynamicSection<ELFT>::addInt(int32_t Tag, uint64_t Val) {
1235 Entries.push_back({Tag, [=] { return Val; }});
1236}

1238template <class ELFT>
1239void DynamicSection<ELFT>::addInSec(int32_t Tag, InputSection *Sec) {
1240 Entries.push_back({Tag, [=] { return Sec->getVA(0); }});
1241}
1242
1243template <class ELFT>
1244void DynamicSection<ELFT>::addInSecRelative(int32_t Tag, InputSection *Sec) {
1245 size_t TagOffset = Entries.size() * Entsize;
1246 Entries.push_back(
1247 {Tag, [=] { return Sec->getVA(0) - (getVA() + TagOffset); }});
1248}

1250template <class ELFT>
1251void DynamicSection<ELFT>::addOutSec(int32_t Tag, OutputSection *Sec) {
1252 Entries.push_back({Tag, [=] { return Sec->Addr; }});
1253}
1254
1255template <class ELFT>
1256void DynamicSection<ELFT>::addSize(int32_t Tag, OutputSection *Sec) {
1257 Entries.push_back({Tag, [=] { return Sec->Size; }});
1258}

1260template <class ELFT>
1261void DynamicSection<ELFT>::addSym(int32_t Tag, Symbol *Sym) {
1262 Entries.push_back({Tag, [=] { return Sym->getVA(); }});
1263}

1265// A Linker script may assign the RELA relocation sections to the same
1266// output section. When this occurs we cannot just use the OutputSection
1267// Size. Moreover the [DT_JMPREL, DT_JMPREL + DT_PLTRELSZ) is permitted to
1268// overlap with the [DT_RELA, DT_RELA + DT_RELASZ).
1269static uint64_t addPltRelSz() {
1270 size_t Size = In.RelaPlt->getSize();
1271 if (In.RelaIplt->getParent() == In.RelaPlt->getParent() &&
1272 In.RelaIplt->Name == In.RelaPlt->Name)
1273 Size += In.RelaIplt->getSize();
1274 return Size;
1275}
1276
1277// Add remaining entries to complete .dynamic contents.
1278template <class ELFT> void DynamicSection<ELFT>::finalizeContents() {
1279 elf::Partition &Part = getPartition();
1280 bool IsMain = Part.Name.empty();
1281
1282 for (StringRef S : Config->FilterList)
1283 addInt(DT_FILTER, Part.DynStrTab->addString(S));
1284 for (StringRef S : Config->AuxiliaryList)
1285 addInt(DT_AUXILIARY, Part.DynStrTab->addString(S));
1286
1287 if (!Config->Rpath.empty())
1288 addInt(Config->EnableNewDtags ? DT_RUNPATH : DT_RPATH,
1289 Part.DynStrTab->addString(Config->Rpath));
1290
1291 for (SharedFile *File : SharedFiles)
1292 if (File->IsNeeded)
1293 addInt(DT_NEEDED, Part.DynStrTab->addString(File->SoName));
1294
1295 if (IsMain) {
1296 if (!Config->SoName.empty())
1297 addInt(DT_SONAME, Part.DynStrTab->addString(Config->SoName));
1298 } else {
1299 if (!Config->SoName.empty())
1300 addInt(DT_NEEDED, Part.DynStrTab->addString(Config->SoName));
1301 addInt(DT_SONAME, Part.DynStrTab->addString(Part.Name));
1302 }
1303
1304 // Set DT_FLAGS and DT_FLAGS_1.
1305 uint32_t DtFlags = 0;
1306 uint32_t DtFlags1 = 0;
1307 if (Config->Bsymbolic)
1308 DtFlags |= DF_SYMBOLIC;
1309 if (Config->ZGlobal)
1310 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_GLOBAL;
1311 if (Config->ZInitfirst)
1312 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_INITFIRST;
1313 if (Config->ZInterpose)
1314 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_INTERPOSE;
1315 if (Config->ZNodefaultlib)
1316 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_NODEFLIB;
1317 if (Config->ZNodelete)
1318 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_NODELETE;
1319 if (Config->ZNodlopen)
1320 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_NOOPEN;
1321 if (Config->ZNow) {
1322 DtFlags |= DF_BIND_NOW;
1323 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_NOW;
1324 }
1325 if (Config->ZOrigin) {
1326 DtFlags |= DF_ORIGIN;
1327 DtFlags1 |= DF_1_ORIGIN;
1328 }
1329 if (!Config->ZText)
1330 DtFlags |= DF_TEXTREL;
1331 if (Config->HasStaticTlsModel)
1332 DtFlags |= DF_STATIC_TLS;
1333
1334 if (DtFlags)
1335 addInt(DT_FLAGS, DtFlags);
1336 if (DtFlags1)
1337 addInt(DT_FLAGS_1, DtFlags1);
1338
1339 // DT_DEBUG is a pointer to debug informaion used by debuggers at runtime. We
1340 // need it for each process, so we don't write it for DSOs. The loader writes
1341 // the pointer into this entry.
1342 //
1343 // DT_DEBUG is the only .dynamic entry that needs to be written to. Some
1344 // systems (currently only Fuchsia OS) provide other means to give the
1345 // debugger this information. Such systems may choose make .dynamic read-only.
1346 // If the target is such a system (used -z rodynamic) don't write DT_DEBUG.
1347 if (!Config->Shared && !Config->Relocatable && !Config->ZRodynamic)
1348 addInt(DT_DEBUG, 0);
1349
1350 if (OutputSection *Sec = Part.DynStrTab->getParent())
1351 this->Link = Sec->SectionIndex;
1352
1353 if (Part.RelaDyn->isNeeded()) {
1354 addInSec(Part.RelaDyn->DynamicTag, Part.RelaDyn);
1355 addSize(Part.RelaDyn->SizeDynamicTag, Part.RelaDyn->getParent());
1356
1357 bool IsRela = Config->IsRela;
1358 addInt(IsRela ? DT_RELAENT : DT_RELENT,
1359 IsRela ? sizeof(Elf_Rela) : sizeof(Elf_Rel));
1360
1361 // MIPS dynamic loader does not support RELCOUNT tag.
1362 // The problem is in the tight relation between dynamic
1363 // relocations and GOT. So do not emit this tag on MIPS.
1364 if (Config->EMachine != EM_MIPS) {
1365 size_t NumRelativeRels = Part.RelaDyn->getRelativeRelocCount();
1366 if (Config->ZCombreloc && NumRelativeRels)
1367 addInt(IsRela ? DT_RELACOUNT : DT_RELCOUNT, NumRelativeRels);
1368 }
1369 }
1370 if (Part.RelrDyn && !Part.RelrDyn->Relocs.empty()) {
1371 addInSec(Config->UseAndroidRelrTags ? DT_ANDROID_RELR : DT_RELR,
1372 Part.RelrDyn);
1373 addSize(Config->UseAndroidRelrTags ? DT_ANDROID_RELRSZ : DT_RELRSZ,
1374 Part.RelrDyn->getParent());
1375 addInt(Config->UseAndroidRelrTags ? DT_ANDROID_RELRENT : DT_RELRENT,
1376 sizeof(Elf_Relr));
1377 }
1378 // .rel[a].plt section usually consists of two parts, containing plt and
1379 // iplt relocations. It is possible to have only iplt relocations in the
1380 // output. In that case RelaPlt is empty and have zero offset, the same offset
1381 // as RelaIplt have. And we still want to emit proper dynamic tags for that
1382 // case, so here we always use RelaPlt as marker for the begining of
1383 // .rel[a].plt section.
1384 if (IsMain && In.RelaPlt->getParent()->isLive()) {
1385 addInSec(DT_JMPREL, In.RelaPlt);
1386 Entries.push_back({DT_PLTRELSZ, addPltRelSz});
1387 switch (Config->EMachine) {
1388 case EM_MIPS:
1389 addInSec(DT_MIPS_PLTGOT, In.GotPlt);
1390 break;
1391 case EM_SPARCV9:
1392 addInSec(DT_PLTGOT, In.Plt);
1393 break;
1394 default:
1395 addInSec(DT_PLTGOT, In.GotPlt);
1396 break;
1397 }
1398 addInt(DT_PLTREL, Config->IsRela ? DT_RELA : DT_REL);
1399 }
1400
1401 if (Config->EMachine == EM_AARCH64) {
1402 if (Config->AndFeatures & GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_BTI)
1403 addInt(DT_AARCH64_BTI_PLT, 0);
1404 if (Config->AndFeatures & GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_PAC)
1405 addInt(DT_AARCH64_PAC_PLT, 0);
1406 }
1407
1408 addInSec(DT_SYMTAB, Part.DynSymTab);
1409 addInt(DT_SYMENT, sizeof(Elf_Sym));
1410 addInSec(DT_STRTAB, Part.DynStrTab);
1411 addInt(DT_STRSZ, Part.DynStrTab->getSize());
1412 if (!Config->ZText)
1413 addInt(DT_TEXTREL, 0);
1414 if (Part.GnuHashTab)
1415 addInSec(DT_GNU_HASH, Part.GnuHashTab);
1416 if (Part.HashTab)
1417 addInSec(DT_HASH, Part.HashTab);
1418
1419 if (IsMain) {
1420 if (Out::PreinitArray) {
1421 addOutSec(DT_PREINIT_ARRAY, Out::PreinitArray);
1422 addSize(DT_PREINIT_ARRAYSZ, Out::PreinitArray);
1423 }
1424 if (Out::InitArray) {
1425 addOutSec(DT_INIT_ARRAY, Out::InitArray);
1426 addSize(DT_INIT_ARRAYSZ, Out::InitArray);
1427 }
1428 if (Out::FiniArray) {
1429 addOutSec(DT_FINI_ARRAY, Out::FiniArray);
1430 addSize(DT_FINI_ARRAYSZ, Out::FiniArray);
1431 }
1432
1433 if (Symbol *B = Symtab->find(Config->Init))
1434 if (B->isDefined())
1435 addSym(DT_INIT, B);
1436 if (Symbol *B = Symtab->find(Config->Fini))
1437 if (B->isDefined())
1438 addSym(DT_FINI, B);
1439 }
1440
1441 bool HasVerNeed = SharedFile::VernauxNum != 0;
1442 if (HasVerNeed || Part.VerDef)
1443 addInSec(DT_VERSYM, Part.VerSym);
1444 if (Part.VerDef) {
1445 addInSec(DT_VERDEF, Part.VerDef);
1446 addInt(DT_VERDEFNUM, getVerDefNum());
1447 }
1448 if (HasVerNeed) {
1449 addInSec(DT_VERNEED, Part.VerNeed);
1450 unsigned NeedNum = 0;
1451 for (SharedFile *F : SharedFiles)
1452 if (!F->Vernauxs.empty())
1453 ++NeedNum;
1454 addInt(DT_VERNEEDNUM, NeedNum);
1455 }
1456
1457 if (Config->EMachine == EM_MIPS) {
1458 addInt(DT_MIPS_RLD_VERSION, 1);
1459 addInt(DT_MIPS_FLAGS, RHF_NOTPOT);
1460 addInt(DT_MIPS_BASE_ADDRESS, Target->getImageBase());
1461 addInt(DT_MIPS_SYMTABNO, Part.DynSymTab->getNumSymbols());
1462
1463 add(DT_MIPS_LOCAL_GOTNO, [] { return In.MipsGot->getLocalEntriesNum(); });
1464
1465 if (const Symbol *B = In.MipsGot->getFirstGlobalEntry())
1466 addInt(DT_MIPS_GOTSYM, B->DynsymIndex);
1467 else
1468 addInt(DT_MIPS_GOTSYM, Part.DynSymTab->getNumSymbols());
1469 addInSec(DT_PLTGOT, In.MipsGot);
1470 if (In.MipsRldMap) {
1471 if (!Config->Pie && !Config->Shared)
1472 addInSec(DT_MIPS_RLD_MAP, In.MipsRldMap);
1473 // Store the offset to the .rld_map section
1474 // relative to the address of the tag.
1475 addInSecRelative(DT_MIPS_RLD_MAP_REL, In.MipsRldMap);
1476 }
1477 uint64_t TargetCheriFlags = 0;
1478 if (Config->isCheriABI()) {
1479 if (InX<ELFT>::MipsAbiFlags)
1480 if (auto ABI = InX<ELFT>::MipsAbiFlags->getCheriAbiVariant())
1481 TargetCheriFlags |= *ABI;
1482 // if (Config->CapTableScope != CapTableScopePolicy::All)
1483 // Add the captable scope to the CHERI flags:
1484 TargetCheriFlags |= ((unsigned)Config->CapTableScope) << 3;
1485 if (Config->RelativeCapRelocsOnly)
1486 TargetCheriFlags |= DF_MIPS_CHERI_RELATIVE_CAPRELOCS;
1487 addInt(DT_MIPS_CHERI_FLAGS, TargetCheriFlags);
1488 }
1489 // CHeck that we didn't link incompatible libraries:
1490 for (InputFile *File : SharedFiles) {
1491 auto *F = cast<SharedFile>(File);
1492 // Add an e_flags check here for CHERI-MIPS to avoid linking between
1493 // incompatible libraries:
1494 if (F->IsNeeded)
1495 checkMipsShlibCompatible(F, F->CheriFlags, TargetCheriFlags);
1496 }
1497 if (In.CheriCapTable && In.CheriCapTable->isNeeded()) {
1498 addInSec(DT_MIPS_CHERI_CAPTABLE, In.CheriCapTable);
1499 addSize(DT_MIPS_CHERI_CAPTABLESZ, In.CheriCapTable->getParent());
1500 }
1501 if (In.CheriCapTableMapping && In.CheriCapTableMapping->isNeeded()) {
1502 addInSec(DT_MIPS_CHERI_CAPTABLE_MAPPING, In.CheriCapTableMapping);
1503 addSize(DT_MIPS_CHERI_CAPTABLE_MAPPINGSZ, In.CheriCapTableMapping->getParent());
1504 }
1505 if (InX<ELFT>::CapRelocs && InX<ELFT>::CapRelocs->isNeeded()) {
1506 addInSec(DT_MIPS_CHERI___CAPRELOCS, InX<ELFT>::CapRelocs);
1507 addSize(DT_MIPS_CHERI___CAPRELOCSSZ, InX<ELFT>::CapRelocs->getParent());
1508 }
1509 }
1510
1511 // DT_PPC_GOT indicates to glibc Secure PLT is used. If DT_PPC_GOT is absent,
1512 // glibc assumes the old-style BSS PLT layout which we don't support.
1513 if (Config->EMachine == EM_PPC)
1514 add(DT_PPC_GOT, [] { return In.Got->getVA(); });
1515
1516 // Glink dynamic tag is required by the V2 abi if the plt section isn't empty.
1517 if (Config->EMachine == EM_PPC64 && In.Plt->isNeeded()) {
1518 // The Glink tag points to 32 bytes before the first lazy symbol resolution
1519 // stub, which starts directly after the header.
1520 Entries.push_back({DT_PPC64_GLINK, [=] {
1521 unsigned Offset = Target->PltHeaderSize - 32;
1522 return In.Plt->getVA(0) + Offset;
1523 }});
1524 }
1525
1526 addInt(DT_NULL, 0);
1527
1528 getParent()->Link = this->Link;
1529 this->Size = Entries.size() * this->Entsize;
1530}
1531
1532template <class ELFT> void DynamicSection<ELFT>::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
1533 auto *P = reinterpret_cast<Elf_Dyn *>(Buf);
1534
1535 for (std::pair<int32_t, std::function<uint64_t()>> &KV : Entries) {
1536 P->d_tag = KV.first;
1537 P->d_un.d_val = KV.second();
1538 ++P;
1539 }
1540}

1542uint64_t DynamicReloc::getOffset() const {
1543 return InputSec->getVA(OffsetInSec);
1544}
1545
1546int64_t DynamicReloc::computeAddend() const {
1547 if (UseSymVA)
1548 return Sym->getVA(Addend);
1549 if (!OutputSec)
1550 return Addend;
1551 // See the comment in the DynamicReloc ctor.
1552 return getMipsPageAddr(OutputSec->Addr) + Addend;
1553}
1554
1555uint32_t DynamicReloc::getSymIndex(SymbolTableBaseSection *SymTab) const {
1556 if (Sym && !UseSymVA) {
1557 // It is fine to have a dynsymindex of 0 for the TLS module relocations
1558 if (Sym->DynsymIndex == 0 && Type != Target->TlsModuleIndexRel) {
1559 warn("DynsymIndex == 0 for " + toString(Type) + " relocation against " +
1560 verboseToString(Sym) + "+" + Twine(Addend));
1561 }
1562 return SymTab->getSymbolIndex(Sym);
1563 }
1564 return 0;
1565}

1569 int32_t SizeDynamicTag)
1570 : SyntheticSection(SHF_ALLOC, Type, Config->Wordsize, Name),

1573void RelocationBaseSection::addReloc(RelType DynType, InputSectionBase *IS,
1574 uint64_t OffsetInSec, Symbol *Sym) {
1575 addReloc({DynType, IS, OffsetInSec, false, Sym, 0});
1576}
1577
1578void RelocationBaseSection::addReloc(RelType DynType,
1579 InputSectionBase *InputSec,
1580 uint64_t OffsetInSec, Symbol *Sym,
1581 int64_t Addend, RelExpr Expr,
1582 RelType Type) {
1583 // Write the addends to the relocated address if required. We skip
1584 // it if the written value would be zero.
1585 bool WriteAddend = Config->WriteAddends && (Expr != R_ADDEND || Addend != 0);
1586 // If we are adding a dynamic R_CHERI_CAPABILITY relocation we need to write
1587 // the added to the output file since it will be initialized to 0xcacacaca
1588 if (Expr == R_CHERI_CAPABILITY)
1589 Expr = R_ADDEND;
1590 if (WriteAddend)
1591 InputSec->Relocations.push_back({Expr, Type, OffsetInSec, Addend, Sym});
1592 addReloc({DynType, InputSec, OffsetInSec, Expr != R_ADDEND, Sym, Addend});
1593}
1594
1595void RelocationBaseSection::addReloc(const DynamicReloc &Reloc) {
1596 if (Reloc.Type == Target->RelativeRel)
1597 ++NumRelativeRelocs;
1598 Relocs.push_back(Reloc);
1599 auto IS = Reloc.InputSec;
1600 if (!Config->IsRela && IS->AreRelocsRela) {
1601 // HACK for FreeBSD mips n64/CHERI: input is RELA, output is REL -> write the addend to the output
1602 // But don't do it for R_MIPS_CHERI_CAPABILITY relocations since they are handled differently
1603 // TODO: remove this hack
1604 if (Reloc.Type != R_MIPS_CHERI_CAPABILITY)
1605 const_cast<InputSectionBase*>(IS)->FreeBSDMipsRelocationsHack.push_back(Reloc);
1606 }
1607 if (Config->isCheriABI() && Config->RelativeCapRelocsOnly &&
1608 Reloc.InputSec->Name == "__cap_relocs") {
1609 warn("attempting to add a dynamic relocation against the __cap_relocs "
1610 "section. If this is intended pass --no-relative-cap-relocs.");
1611 }
1612 if (Config->EMachine == EM_MIPS && Config->BuildingFreeBSDRtld) {
1613 unsigned BaseRelocType = Reloc.Type & 0xff;
1614 if (BaseRelocType != R_MIPS_REL32 && BaseRelocType != R_MIPS_NONE)
1615 error("relocation " + toString(Reloc.Type) + " against " +
1616 toString(*Reloc.Sym) + " cannot be using when building FreeBSD RTLD" +
1617 getLocationMessage(*Reloc.InputSec, *Reloc.Sym, Reloc.OffsetInSec));
1618 }
1619}

1621void RelocationBaseSection::finalizeContents() {
1622 SymbolTableBaseSection *SymTab = getPartition().DynSymTab;
1623
1624 // When linking glibc statically, .rel{,a}.plt contains R_*_IRELATIVE
1625 // relocations due to IFUNC (e.g. strcpy). sh_link will be set to 0 in that
1626 // case.
1627 if (SymTab && SymTab->getParent())
1628 getParent()->Link = SymTab->getParent()->SectionIndex;
1629 else
1630 getParent()->Link = 0;
1631
1632 if (Config->isCheriABI() && In.CheriCapTable && In.CheriCapTable->isNeeded()) {
1633 assert(In.CheriCapTable->getParent()->SectionIndex != UINT32_MAX);
1634 // For MIPS CheriABI we use the captable as the sh_info value
1635 if (In.RelaPlt == this)
1636 getParent()->Info = In.CheriCapTable->getParent()->SectionIndex;
1637 if (In.RelaIplt == this)
1638 getParent()->Info = In.CheriCapTable->getParent()->SectionIndex;
1639 } else {
1640 if (In.RelaPlt == this)
1641 getParent()->Info = In.GotPlt->getParent()->SectionIndex;
1642 if (In.RelaIplt == this)
1643 getParent()->Info = In.IgotPlt->getParent()->SectionIndex;
1644 }
1645 assert(getParent()->Info != UINT32_MAX);
1646}

1653template <class ELFT>
1654static void encodeDynamicReloc(SymbolTableBaseSection *SymTab,
1655 typename ELFT::Rela *P,
1656 const DynamicReloc &Rel) {
1657 if (Config->IsRela)
1658 P->r_addend = Rel.computeAddend();
1659 P->r_offset = Rel.getOffset();
1660 P->setSymbolAndType(Rel.getSymIndex(SymTab), Rel.Type, Config->IsMips64EL);
1661}

1663template <class ELFT>
1664RelocationSection<ELFT>::RelocationSection(StringRef Name, bool Sort)
1665 : RelocationBaseSection(Name, Config->IsRela ? SHT_RELA : SHT_REL,
1666 Config->IsRela ? DT_RELA : DT_REL,
1667 Config->IsRela ? DT_RELASZ : DT_RELSZ),
1668 Sort(Sort) {
1669 this->Entsize = Config->IsRela ? sizeof(Elf_Rela) : sizeof(Elf_Rel);
1670}
1671
1672template <class ELFT> void RelocationSection<ELFT>::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
1673 SymbolTableBaseSection *SymTab = getPartition().DynSymTab;
1674
1675 // Sort by (!IsRelative,SymIndex,r_offset). DT_REL[A]COUNT requires us to
1676 // place R_*_RELATIVE first. SymIndex is to improve locality, while r_offset
1677 // is to make results easier to read.
1678 if (Sort)
1679 llvm::stable_sort(
1680 Relocs, [&](const DynamicReloc &A, const DynamicReloc &B) {
1681 return std::make_tuple(A.Type != Target->RelativeRel,
1682 A.getSymIndex(SymTab), A.getOffset()) <
1683 std::make_tuple(B.Type != Target->RelativeRel,
1684 B.getSymIndex(SymTab), B.getOffset());
1685 });
1686
1687 for (const DynamicReloc &Rel : Relocs) {
1688 encodeDynamicReloc<ELFT>(SymTab, reinterpret_cast<Elf_Rela *>(Buf), Rel);
1689 Buf += Config->IsRela ? sizeof(Elf_Rela) : sizeof(Elf_Rel);
1690 }
1691}

1693template <class ELFT>
1694AndroidPackedRelocationSection<ELFT>::AndroidPackedRelocationSection(
1695 StringRef Name)
1696 : RelocationBaseSection(
1697 Name, Config->IsRela ? SHT_ANDROID_RELA : SHT_ANDROID_REL,
1698 Config->IsRela ? DT_ANDROID_RELA : DT_ANDROID_REL,
1699 Config->IsRela ? DT_ANDROID_RELASZ : DT_ANDROID_RELSZ) {
1700 this->Entsize = 1;
1701}
1702
1703template <class ELFT>
1704bool AndroidPackedRelocationSection<ELFT>::updateAllocSize() {
1705 // This function computes the contents of an Android-format packed relocation
1706 // section.
1707 //
1708 // This format compresses relocations by using relocation groups to factor out
1709 // fields that are common between relocations and storing deltas from previous
1710 // relocations in SLEB128 format (which has a short representation for small
1711 // numbers). A good example of a relocation type with common fields is
1712 // R_*_RELATIVE, which is normally used to represent function pointers in
1713 // vtables. In the REL format, each relative relocation has the same r_info
1714 // field, and is only different from other relative relocations in terms of
1715 // the r_offset field. By sorting relocations by offset, grouping them by
1716 // r_info and representing each relocation with only the delta from the
1717 // previous offset, each 8-byte relocation can be compressed to as little as 1
1718 // byte (or less with run-length encoding). This relocation packer was able to
1719 // reduce the size of the relocation section in an Android Chromium DSO from
1720 // 2,911,184 bytes to 174,693 bytes, or 6% of the original size.
1721 //
1722 // A relocation section consists of a header containing the literal bytes
1723 // 'APS2' followed by a sequence of SLEB128-encoded integers. The first two
1724 // elements are the total number of relocations in the section and an initial
1725 // r_offset value. The remaining elements define a sequence of relocation
1726 // groups. Each relocation group starts with a header consisting of the
1727 // following elements:
1728 //
1729 // - the number of relocations in the relocation group
1730 // - flags for the relocation group
1731 // - (if RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_OFFSET_DELTA_FLAG is set) the r_offset delta
1732 // for each relocation in the group.
1733 // - (if RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_INFO_FLAG is set) the value of the r_info
1734 // field for each relocation in the group.
1735 // - (if RELOCATION_GROUP_HAS_ADDEND_FLAG and
1736 // RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_ADDEND_FLAG are set) the r_addend delta for
1737 // each relocation in the group.
1738 //
1739 // Following the relocation group header are descriptions of each of the
1740 // relocations in the group. They consist of the following elements:
1741 //
1742 // - (if RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_OFFSET_DELTA_FLAG is not set) the r_offset
1743 // delta for this relocation.
1744 // - (if RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_INFO_FLAG is not set) the value of the r_info
1745 // field for this relocation.
1746 // - (if RELOCATION_GROUP_HAS_ADDEND_FLAG is set and
1747 // RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_ADDEND_FLAG is not set) the r_addend delta for
1748 // this relocation.
1749
1750 size_t OldSize = RelocData.size();
1751
1752 RelocData = {'A', 'P', 'S', '2'};
1753 raw_svector_ostream OS(RelocData);
1754 auto Add = [&](int64_t V) { encodeSLEB128(V, OS); };
1755
1756 // The format header includes the number of relocations and the initial
1757 // offset (we set this to zero because the first relocation group will
1758 // perform the initial adjustment).
1759 Add(Relocs.size());
1760 Add(0);
1761
1762 std::vector<Elf_Rela> Relatives, NonRelatives;
1763
1764 for (const DynamicReloc &Rel : Relocs) {
1765 Elf_Rela R;
1766 encodeDynamicReloc<ELFT>(getPartition().DynSymTab, &R, Rel);
1767
1768 if (R.getType(Config->IsMips64EL) == Target->RelativeRel)
1769 Relatives.push_back(R);
1770 else
1771 NonRelatives.push_back(R);
1772 }
1773
1774 llvm::sort(Relatives, [](const Elf_Rel &A, const Elf_Rel &B) {
1775 return A.r_offset < B.r_offset;
1776 });
1777
1778 // Try to find groups of relative relocations which are spaced one word
1779 // apart from one another. These generally correspond to vtable entries. The
1780 // format allows these groups to be encoded using a sort of run-length
1781 // encoding, but each group will cost 7 bytes in addition to the offset from
1782 // the previous group, so it is only profitable to do this for groups of
1783 // size 8 or larger.
1784 std::vector<Elf_Rela> UngroupedRelatives;
1785 std::vector<std::vector<Elf_Rela>> RelativeGroups;
1786 for (auto I = Relatives.begin(), E = Relatives.end(); I != E;) {
1787 std::vector<Elf_Rela> Group;
1788 do {
1789 Group.push_back(*I++);
1790 } while (I != E && (I - 1)->r_offset + Config->Wordsize == I->r_offset);
1791
1792 if (Group.size() < 8)
1793 UngroupedRelatives.insert(UngroupedRelatives.end(), Group.begin(),
1794 Group.end());
1795 else
1796 RelativeGroups.emplace_back(std::move(Group));
1797 }
1798
1799 unsigned HasAddendIfRela =
1800 Config->IsRela ? RELOCATION_GROUP_HAS_ADDEND_FLAG : 0;
1801
1802 uint64_t Offset = 0;
1803 uint64_t Addend = 0;
1804
1805 // Emit the run-length encoding for the groups of adjacent relative
1806 // relocations. Each group is represented using two groups in the packed
1807 // format. The first is used to set the current offset to the start of the
1808 // group (and also encodes the first relocation), and the second encodes the
1809 // remaining relocations.
1810 for (std::vector<Elf_Rela> &G : RelativeGroups) {
1811 // The first relocation in the group.
1812 Add(1);
1813 Add(RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_OFFSET_DELTA_FLAG |
1814 RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_INFO_FLAG | HasAddendIfRela);
1815 Add(G[0].r_offset - Offset);
1816 Add(Target->RelativeRel);
1817 if (Config->IsRela) {
1818 Add(G[0].r_addend - Addend);
1819 Addend = G[0].r_addend;
1820 }
1821
1822 // The remaining relocations.
1823 Add(G.size() - 1);
1824 Add(RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_OFFSET_DELTA_FLAG |
1825 RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_INFO_FLAG | HasAddendIfRela);
1826 Add(Config->Wordsize);
1827 Add(Target->RelativeRel);
1828 if (Config->IsRela) {
1829 for (auto I = G.begin() + 1, E = G.end(); I != E; ++I) {
1830 Add(I->r_addend - Addend);
1831 Addend = I->r_addend;
1832 }
1833 }
1834
1835 Offset = G.back().r_offset;
1836 }
1837
1838 // Now the ungrouped relatives.
1839 if (!UngroupedRelatives.empty()) {
1840 Add(UngroupedRelatives.size());
1841 Add(RELOCATION_GROUPED_BY_INFO_FLAG | HasAddendIfRela);
1842 Add(Target->RelativeRel);
1843 for (Elf_Rela &R : UngroupedRelatives) {
1844 Add(R.r_offset - Offset);
1845 Offset = R.r_offset;
1846 if (Config->IsRela) {
1847 Add(R.r_addend - Addend);
1848 Addend = R.r_addend;
1849 }
1850 }
1851 }
1852
1853 // Finally the non-relative relocations.
1854 llvm::sort(NonRelatives, [](const Elf_Rela &A, const Elf_Rela &B) {
1855 return A.r_offset < B.r_offset;
1856 });
1857 if (!NonRelatives.empty()) {
1858 Add(NonRelatives.size());
1859 Add(HasAddendIfRela);
1860 for (Elf_Rela &R : NonRelatives) {
1861 Add(R.r_offset - Offset);
1862 Offset = R.r_offset;
1863 Add(R.r_info);
1864 if (Config->IsRela) {
1865 Add(R.r_addend - Addend);
1866 Addend = R.r_addend;
1867 }
1868 }
1869 }
1870
1871 // Don't allow the section to shrink; otherwise the size of the section can
1872 // oscillate infinitely.
1873 if (RelocData.size() < OldSize)
1874 RelocData.append(OldSize - RelocData.size(), 0);
1875
1876 // Returns whether the section size changed. We need to keep recomputing both
1877 // section layout and the contents of this section until the size converges
1878 // because changing this section's size can affect section layout, which in
1879 // turn can affect the sizes of the LEB-encoded integers stored in this
1880 // section.
1881 return RelocData.size() != OldSize;
1882}

1885 this->Entsize = Config->Wordsize;
1886}
1887
1888template <class ELFT> bool RelrSection<ELFT>::updateAllocSize() {
1889 // This function computes the contents of an SHT_RELR packed relocation
1890 // section.
1891 //
1892 // Proposal for adding SHT_RELR sections to generic-abi is here:
1893 // https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/generic-abi/bX460iggiKg
1894 //
1895 // The encoded sequence of Elf64_Relr entries in a SHT_RELR section looks
1896 // like [ AAAAAAAA BBBBBBB1 BBBBBBB1 ... AAAAAAAA BBBBBB1 ... ]
1897 //
1898 // i.e. start with an address, followed by any number of bitmaps. The address
1899 // entry encodes 1 relocation. The subsequent bitmap entries encode up to 63
1900 // relocations each, at subsequent offsets following the last address entry.
1901 //
1902 // The bitmap entries must have 1 in the least significant bit. The assumption
1903 // here is that an address cannot have 1 in lsb. Odd addresses are not
1904 // supported.
1905 //
1906 // Excluding the least significant bit in the bitmap, each non-zero bit in
1907 // the bitmap represents a relocation to be applied to a corresponding machine
1908 // word that follows the base address word. The second least significant bit
1909 // represents the machine word immediately following the initial address, and
1910 // each bit that follows represents the next word, in linear order. As such,
1911 // a single bitmap can encode up to 31 relocations in a 32-bit object, and
1912 // 63 relocations in a 64-bit object.
1913 //
1914 // This encoding has a couple of interesting properties:
1915 // 1. Looking at any entry, it is clear whether it's an address or a bitmap:
1916 // even means address, odd means bitmap.
1917 // 2. Just a simple list of addresses is a valid encoding.
1918
1919 size_t OldSize = RelrRelocs.size();
1920 RelrRelocs.clear();
1921
1922 // Same as Config->Wordsize but faster because this is a compile-time
1923 // constant.
1924 const size_t Wordsize = sizeof(typename ELFT::uint);
1925
1926 // Number of bits to use for the relocation offsets bitmap.
1927 // Must be either 63 or 31.
1928 const size_t NBits = Wordsize * 8 - 1;
1929
1930 // Get offsets for all relative relocations and sort them.
1931 std::vector<uint64_t> Offsets;
1932 for (const RelativeReloc &Rel : Relocs)
1933 Offsets.push_back(Rel.getOffset());
1934 llvm::sort(Offsets);
1935
1936 // For each leading relocation, find following ones that can be folded
1937 // as a bitmap and fold them.
1938 for (size_t I = 0, E = Offsets.size(); I < E;) {
1939 // Add a leading relocation.
1940 RelrRelocs.push_back(Elf_Relr(Offsets[I]));
1941 uint64_t Base = Offsets[I] + Wordsize;
1942 ++I;
1943
1944 // Find foldable relocations to construct bitmaps.
1945 while (I < E) {
1946 uint64_t Bitmap = 0;
1947
1948 while (I < E) {
1949 uint64_t Delta = Offsets[I] - Base;
1950
1951 // If it is too far, it cannot be folded.
1952 if (Delta >= NBits * Wordsize)
1953 break;
1954
1955 // If it is not a multiple of wordsize away, it cannot be folded.
1956 if (Delta % Wordsize)
1957 break;
1958
1959 // Fold it.
1960 Bitmap |= 1ULL << (Delta / Wordsize);
1961 ++I;
1962 }
1963
1964 if (!Bitmap)
1965 break;
1966
1967 RelrRelocs.push_back(Elf_Relr((Bitmap << 1) | 1));
1968 Base += NBits * Wordsize;
1969 }
1970 }
1971
1972 return RelrRelocs.size() != OldSize;
1973}

1975SymbolTableBaseSection::SymbolTableBaseSection(StringTableSection &StrTabSec)
1976 : SyntheticSection(StrTabSec.isDynamic() ? (uint64_t)SHF_ALLOC : 0,
1977 StrTabSec.isDynamic() ? SHT_DYNSYM : SHT_SYMTAB,
1978 Config->Wordsize,
1979 StrTabSec.isDynamic() ? ".dynsym" : ".symtab"),
1980 StrTabSec(StrTabSec) {}
1981
1982// Orders symbols according to their positions in the GOT,
1983// in compliance with MIPS ABI rules.
1984// See "Global Offset Table" in Chapter 5 in the following document
1985// for detailed description:
1986// ftp://www.linux-mips.org/pub/linux/mips/doc/ABI/mipsabi.pdf
1987static bool sortMipsSymbols(const SymbolTableEntry &L,
1988 const SymbolTableEntry &R) {
1989 // Sort entries related to non-local preemptible symbols by GOT indexes.
1990 // All other entries go to the beginning of a dynsym in arbitrary order.
1991 if (L.Sym->isInGot() && R.Sym->isInGot())
1992 return L.Sym->GotIndex < R.Sym->GotIndex;
1993 if (!L.Sym->isInGot() && !R.Sym->isInGot())
1994 return false;
1995 return !L.Sym->isInGot();
1996}
1997
1998void SymbolTableBaseSection::finalizeContents() {
1999 if (OutputSection *Sec = StrTabSec.getParent())
2000 getParent()->Link = Sec->SectionIndex;
2001
2002 if (this->Type != SHT_DYNSYM) {
2003 sortSymTabSymbols();
2004 return;
2005 }
2006
2007 // If it is a .dynsym, there should be no local symbols, but we need
2008 // to do a few things for the dynamic linker.
2009
2010 // Section's Info field has the index of the first non-local symbol.
2011 // Because the first symbol entry is a null entry, 1 is the first.
2012 getParent()->Info = 1;
2013
2014 // XXXAR: in the CheriABI case it is possible that we have local symbols
2015 // in .dynsym (for function pointers in the PLT ABI)
2016 if (Config->isCheriABI()) {
2017 sortSymTabSymbols();
2018 }
2019
2020 if (getPartition().GnuHashTab) {
2021 // NB: It also sorts Symbols to meet the GNU hash table requirements.
2022 getPartition().GnuHashTab->addSymbols(Symbols);
2023 } else if (Config->EMachine == EM_MIPS) {
2024 llvm::stable_sort(Symbols, sortMipsSymbols);
2025 }
2026
2027 // Only the main partition's dynsym indexes are stored in the symbols
2028 // themselves. All other partitions use a lookup table.
2029 if (this == Main->DynSymTab) {
2030 size_t I = 0;
2031 for (const SymbolTableEntry &S : Symbols)
2032 S.Sym->DynsymIndex = ++I;
2033 }
2034}
2035
2036// The ELF spec requires that all local symbols precede global symbols, so we
2037// sort symbol entries in this function. (For .dynsym, we don't do that because
2038// symbols for dynamic linking are inherently all globals.)
2039//
2040// Aside from above, we put local symbols in groups starting with the STT_FILE
2041// symbol. That is convenient for purpose of identifying where are local symbols
2042// coming from.
2043void SymbolTableBaseSection::sortSymTabSymbols() {
2044 // Move all local symbols before global symbols.
2045 auto E = std::stable_partition(
2046 Symbols.begin(), Symbols.end(), [](const SymbolTableEntry &S) {
2047 return S.Sym->isLocal() || S.Sym->computeBinding() == STB_LOCAL;
2048 });
2049 size_t NumLocals = E - Symbols.begin();
2050 getParent()->Info = NumLocals + 1;
2051
2052 // We want to group the local symbols by file. For that we rebuild the local
2053 // part of the symbols vector. We do not need to care about the STT_FILE
2054 // symbols, they are already naturally placed first in each group. That
2055 // happens because STT_FILE is always the first symbol in the object and hence
2056 // precede all other local symbols we add for a file.
2057 MapVector<InputFile *, std::vector<SymbolTableEntry>> Arr;
2058 for (const SymbolTableEntry &S : llvm::make_range(Symbols.begin(), E))
2059 Arr[S.Sym->File].push_back(S);
2060
2061 auto I = Symbols.begin();
2062 for (std::pair<InputFile *, std::vector<SymbolTableEntry>> &P : Arr)
2063 for (SymbolTableEntry &Entry : P.second)
2064 *I++ = Entry;
2065}
2066
2067void SymbolTableBaseSection::addSymbol(Symbol *B) {
2068 // Adding a local symbol to a .dynsym is a bug.
2069 assert(this->Type != SHT_DYNSYM || !B->isLocal());
2070
2071 bool HashIt = B->isLocal();
2072 Symbols.push_back({B, StrTabSec.addString(B->getName(), HashIt)});
2073}

2075size_t SymbolTableBaseSection::getSymbolIndex(Symbol *Sym) {
2076 if (this == Main->DynSymTab)
2077 return Sym->DynsymIndex;
2078
2079 // Initializes symbol lookup tables lazily. This is used only for -r,
2080 // -emit-relocs and dynsyms in partitions other than the main one.
2081 llvm::call_once(OnceFlag, [&] {
2082 SymbolIndexMap.reserve(Symbols.size());
2083 size_t I = 0;
2084 for (const SymbolTableEntry &E : Symbols) {
2085 if (E.Sym->Type == STT_SECTION)
2086 SectionIndexMap[E.Sym->getOutputSection()] = ++I;
2087 else
2088 SymbolIndexMap[E.Sym] = ++I;
2089 }
2090 });
2091
2092 // Section symbols are mapped based on their output sections
2093 // to maintain their semantics.
2094 if (Sym->Type == STT_SECTION)
2095 return SectionIndexMap.lookup(Sym->getOutputSection());
2096 return SymbolIndexMap.lookup(Sym);
2097}

2112static uint32_t getSymSectionIndex(Symbol *Sym) {
2113 if (getCommonSec(Sym))
2114 return SHN_COMMON;
2115 if (!isa<Defined>(Sym) || Sym->NeedsPltAddr)
2116 return SHN_UNDEF;
2117 if (const OutputSection *OS = Sym->getOutputSection())

2123// Write the internal symbol table contents to the output symbol table.
2124template <class ELFT> void SymbolTableSection<ELFT>::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
2125 // The first entry is a null entry as per the ELF spec.
2126 memset(Buf, 0, sizeof(Elf_Sym));
2127 Buf += sizeof(Elf_Sym);
2128
2129 auto *ESym = reinterpret_cast<Elf_Sym *>(Buf);
2130
2131 for (SymbolTableEntry &Ent : Symbols) {
2132 Symbol *Sym = Ent.Sym;
2133 bool IsDefinedHere = Type == SHT_SYMTAB || Sym->Partition == Partition;
2134
2135 // Set st_info and st_other.
2136 ESym->st_other = 0;
2137 if (Sym->isLocal()) {
2138 ESym->setBindingAndType(STB_LOCAL, Sym->Type);
2139 } else {
2140 ESym->setBindingAndType(Sym->computeBinding(), Sym->Type);
2141 ESym->setVisibility(Sym->Visibility);
2142 }
2143
2144 // The 3 most significant bits of st_other are used by OpenPOWER ABI.
2145 // See getPPC64GlobalEntryToLocalEntryOffset() for more details.
2146 if (Config->EMachine == EM_PPC64)
2147 ESym->st_other |= Sym->StOther & 0xe0;
2148
2149 ESym->st_name = Ent.StrTabOffset;
2150 if (IsDefinedHere)
2151 ESym->st_shndx = getSymSectionIndex(Ent.Sym);
2152 else
2153 ESym->st_shndx = 0;
2154
2155 // Copy symbol size if it is a defined symbol. st_size is not significant
2156 // for undefined symbols, so whether copying it or not is up to us if that's
2157 // the case. We'll leave it as zero because by not setting a value, we can
2158 // get the exact same outputs for two sets of input files that differ only
2159 // in undefined symbol size in DSOs.
2160 if (ESym->st_shndx == SHN_UNDEF || !IsDefinedHere)
2161 ESym->st_size = 0;
2162 else
2163 ESym->st_size = Sym->getSize();
2164
2165 // st_value is usually an address of a symbol, but that has a
2166 // special meaining for uninstantiated common symbols (this can
2167 // occur if -r is given).
2168 if (BssSection *CommonSec = getCommonSec(Ent.Sym))
2169 ESym->st_value = CommonSec->Alignment;
2170 else if (IsDefinedHere)
2171 ESym->st_value = Sym->getVA();
2172 else
2173 ESym->st_value = 0;
2174
2175 ++ESym;
2176 }
2177
2178 // On MIPS we need to mark symbol which has a PLT entry and requires
2179 // pointer equality by STO_MIPS_PLT flag. That is necessary to help
2180 // dynamic linker distinguish such symbols and MIPS lazy-binding stubs.
2181 // https://sourceware.org/ml/binutils/2008-07/txt00000.txt
2182 if (Config->EMachine == EM_MIPS) {
2183 auto *ESym = reinterpret_cast<Elf_Sym *>(Buf);
2184
2185 for (SymbolTableEntry &Ent : Symbols) {
2186 Symbol *Sym = Ent.Sym;
2187 if (Sym->isInPlt() && Sym->NeedsPltAddr)
2188 ESym->st_other |= STO_MIPS_PLT;
2189 if (isMicroMips()) {
2190 // We already set the less-significant bit for symbols
2191 // marked by the `STO_MIPS_MICROMIPS` flag and for microMIPS PLT
2192 // records. That allows us to distinguish such symbols in
2193 // the `MIPS<ELFT>::relocateOne()` routine. Now we should
2194 // clear that bit for non-dynamic symbol table, so tools
2195 // like `objdump` will be able to deal with a correct
2196 // symbol position.
2197 if (Sym->isDefined() &&
2198 ((Sym->StOther & STO_MIPS_MICROMIPS) || Sym->NeedsPltAddr)) {
2199 if (!StrTabSec.isDynamic())
2200 ESym->st_value &= ~1;
2201 ESym->st_other |= STO_MIPS_MICROMIPS;
2202 }
2203 }
2204 if (Config->Relocatable)
2205 if (auto *D = dyn_cast<Defined>(Sym))
2206 if (isMipsPIC<ELFT>(D))
2207 ESym->st_other |= STO_MIPS_PIC;
2208 ++ESym;
2209 }
2210 }
2211}

2218void SymtabShndxSection::writeTo(uint8_t *Buf) {
2219 // We write an array of 32 bit values, where each value has 1:1 association
2220 // with an entry in .symtab. If the corresponding entry contains SHN_XINDEX,
2221 // we need to write actual index, otherwise, we must write SHN_UNDEF(0).
2222 Buf += 4; // Ignore .symtab[0] entry.
2223 for (const SymbolTableEntry &Entry : In.SymTab->getSymbols()) {
2224 if (getSymSectionIndex(Entry.Sym) == SHN_XINDEX)
2225 write32(Buf, Entry.Sym->getOutputSection()->SectionIndex);
2226 Buf += 4;
2227 }

2230bool SymtabShndxSection::isNeeded() const {
2231 // SHT_SYMTAB can hold symbols with section indices values up to
2232 // SHN_LORESERVE. If we need more, we want to use extension SHT_SYMTAB_SHNDX
2233 // section. Problem is that we reveal the final section indices a bit too
2234 // late, and we do not know them here. For simplicity, we just always create
2235 // a .symtab_shndx section when the amount of output sections is huge.
2236 size_t Size = 0;
2237 for (BaseCommand *Base : Script->SectionCommands)
2238 if (isa<OutputSection>(Base))
2239 ++Size;
2240 return Size >= SHN_LORESERVE;
